  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Mapping Data Locations**\n\nI\'m making good progress! I\'ve decided to create a `/src/data.ts` file to keep all static data separate from the components, increasing modularity. Packages, reviews, FAQs, videos, and other data will be stored here. Now, I\'m focusing on accurately mapping the Bengal texts to packages.\n\n\n**Defining Package and Review Data**\n\nI\'ve moved on to fleshing out the specific data structures. I\'m currently defining the object properties for product packages, including IDs, titles in Bengali, capsule counts, prices, and even \"best offer\" labels. I\'m also creating reviews, and considering rating scales and relevant Bengali text. I think I\'ll make a `package.ts` and `review.ts` file, keeping them nicely structured.\n\n\n**Analyzing User Feedback**\n\nI\'m now diving into user feedback and FAQs. I\'ve got a user review from \'\340\246\206\340\246\254\340\247\215\340\246\246\340\247\201\340\246\262 \340\246\225\340\246\260\340\246\277\340\246\256\', with a five-star rating, noting the quick delivery and lack of side effects, which is great. I\'ve also processed two FAQs. I think I will use the feedback to refine the product explanations. I am making good progress.\n\n\n**Addressing FAQs and Videos**\n\nI\'m now integrating more content. I\'ve translated two more FAQs: one about usage during pregnancy, and another clarifying dosage timing \342\200\223 morning and night, 30 minutes before meals, for optimal results. I\'m also preparing to integrate a video about Unani medicine\'s role in diabetes management, with the title \"Expert Advice\" and a subtitle.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create a data file `/src/data.ts` to keep large static text objects and lists out of our UI component code. This keeps our code highly clean, readable, and easy to maintain. We will translate all the literal texts of D-CURE Plus exactly as shown in the screenshot."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 3
      nanos: 733553068
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
