    thinking: "**Designing Interactive Components**\n\nOkay, I\'m now focusing on the interactive sub-components. I\'m thinking about the user experience. For example, when someone clicks \"\340\246\217\340\246\226\340\246\250\340\246\207 \340\246\205\340\246\260\340\247\215\340\246\241\340\246\276\340\246\260 \340\246\225\340\246\260\340\247\201\340\246\250\" (Order Now), I want it to smoothly scroll down to the checkout form. That\'s a good start.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the `/src/components/Navbar.tsx` component. It implements standard navigation items with a link to scroll smoothly to sections such as Benefits, Videos, reviews, and the final booking form. It matches the screenshot perfectly, styling with the primary deep green of D-CURE Plus."
